{
  "task": "MNIST unconditional generation",
  "image_size": 28,
  "channels": 1,
  "training": {
    "epochs": 300,
    "batch_size": 128,
    "lr": 1e-4,
    "schedule": "cosine",
    "parameterization": "v",
    "ddim_steps": 50,
    "ema_decay": 0.9999,
    "patch_size": 4,
    "dim": 128,
    "depth": 4,
    "num_heads": 4,
    "timestep_dim": 128
  },
  "metric": {
    "name": "Frechet MNIST Distance (classifier-based)",
    "feature_extractor": "MNISTClassifier (metrics/classifier.py)",
    "feature_extractor_weights": "metrics/weights/mnist_classifier.pt",
    "feature_extractor_test_acc": 0.943,
    "embedding_dim": 64,
    "n_real": 10000,
    "n_generated": 10000,
    "implementation": "metrics/evaluate.py"
  },
  "runs": [
    {
      "id": "A",
      "name": "wave + physics + self-cond",
      "attention": "wave (2D radial FFT)",
      "conditioning": "physics",
      "self_cond": true,
      "params": 1276800,
      "final_train_loss": 0.02359,
      "low_t_mse": 3.5263,
      "frechet_mnist_distance": 2.194,
      "confident_accuracy": 0.917,
      "class_entropy": 2.286,
      "class_entropy_uniform": 2.303,
      "checkpoint": "outputs/mnist_v7_selfcond/checkpoint_epoch0300.pt"
    },
    {
      "id": "B",
      "name": "standard + physics",
      "attention": "softmax",
      "conditioning": "physics",
      "self_cond": false,
      "params": 1191952,
      "final_train_loss": 0.02305,
      "low_t_mse": 3.8525,
      "frechet_mnist_distance": 4.178,
      "confident_accuracy": 0.890,
      "class_entropy": 2.292,
      "class_entropy_uniform": 2.303,
      "checkpoint": "outputs/mnist_standard_physics/checkpoint_epoch0300.pt"
    },
    {
      "id": "C",
      "name": "standard + AdaLN",
      "attention": "softmax",
      "conditioning": "AdaLN-Zero",
      "self_cond": false,
      "params": 1354768,
      "final_train_loss": 0.02272,
      "low_t_mse": 5.9188,
      "frechet_mnist_distance": 4.803,
      "confident_accuracy": 0.892,
      "class_entropy": 2.292,
      "class_entropy_uniform": 2.303,
      "checkpoint": "outputs/mnist_standard_adaln/checkpoint_epoch0300.pt"
    }
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Run A uses self-conditioning (Chen 2022); runs B and C do not. Self-conditioning is known to substantially improve diffusion sample quality, so A's FMD advantage cannot be cleanly attributed to wave kernels alone. Within the matched no-self-cond cohort (B vs C), physics conditioning gives ~15% better FMD than AdaLN — the opposite of the CIFAR result."
  ],
  "headline_findings": [
    "Within the no-self-cond cohort (B vs C), physics conditioning beats AdaLN on FMD by ~15%.",
    "This is the opposite of the CIFAR ranking, where AdaLN beats physics on FID. The two datasets disagree on which conditioning helps sample quality.",
    "Run A (wave + physics + self-cond) achieves FMD 2.19, the best in the project — but the self-cond confound prevents a clean attribution to the wave kernel.",
    "All three configurations produce near-uniform class distributions (entropy ≈ 2.29 vs uniform 2.30) — no mode collapse on MNIST."
  ],
  "provenance": {
    "git_commit": "076659d",
    "eval_date": "2026-05-19"
  }
}
